<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/ray-kemp> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Ray Kemp was appointed to the Committee on Radioactive Waste Management in November 2019. Ray has been a Member of the Advisory Committee on Carcinogenicity of Chemicals in Foods, Consumer Products and the Environment (COC) Public Interest Representative at the UK Department of Health and Social Care from 2013. In the past, he has worked as an adviser to the Independent Advisory Panel (IAP) for the Australian National Radioactive Waste Management Facility Project. He has also worked as a Member, then Chair of the Radiation Health and Safety Advisory Council of the Australian Radiation Protection and Nuclear Safety Agency (ARPANSA) between 2012 and 2015. Appointed: November 2019 Term ends: November 2023 Reappointed: November 2023 Term ends: November 2027"@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
